# Security & Privacy

## Policy Engine

- Route access decisions through `apps/api/src/lambda/policy_engine.py` instead of adding inline allow/deny branches.
- Keep policy outputs deterministic: `allow`, `decision_code`, `http_status`, `message`, and safe `metadata`.
- Never include PHI/PII in policy metadata, error messages, or logs.
- Gate sensitive audit expansion (`expandSensitive`) with `PHI_APPROVED_GROUP` checks through the policy engine.

## Policy Decision Logging

- All allow/deny decisions MUST originate from `policy_engine`.
- Decisions SHOULD be logged for observability via `policy.policy_decisions`.
- Logged records MUST NOT include request/response payloads.
- Logged records MUST NOT include PHI/PII.

## Mission Control

- Mission Control views in Admin UI must remain metadata-only.
- Mission Control must never return, log, or render request/response payload content or PHI/PII.

## Mission Control Observability

- Mission Control endpoints must never return request or response payloads.
- Only metadata fields are allowed (for example: `vendorCode`, `operationCode`, `decisionCode`, `statusCode`).
- Activity feed must be admin-only.
- Real-time polling must enforce lookback limits.


## Policy Simulation

- Policy simulation must never execute integrations.
- Policy simulation must never log decisions.
- Policy simulation must require admin access.
